text: <@U02F8LF2X|chewbacca> set the channel purpose: projector art
so we have a front projection setup with the old crappy projector and a piece of foamboard
holds up pretty well with ambient light
viewing angle is ergonomically a little weird
might want to pull it up toward the ceiling ~4 inches
oh and for the new building: it would be neat to have some sort of little hallway with a dropped ceiling out of rear projection material so people didn't realize it was a projectable surface
here is the link to the ultra short throw projector: <http://www.bhphotovideo.com/c/product/1170669-REG/hitachi_cp_aw3005_ultra_short_throw.html>
